FBIS3-15346 "drsov043_v_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 Lithuania Ministry Protests Delayed Withdrawal From Estonia WS0303210194 Tallinn BNS in English 1846 GMT 3 Mar 94 WS0303210194 Tallinn BNS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vilnius, Mar 03, BNS -- The Lithuanian Foreign Ministry expressed deep concern about Russia's statement March 2 that it would not withdraw its troops from Estonia by Aug. 31 as was promised earlier. In a statement released Thursday, the Lithuanian ministry said "the Republic of Lithuania once again confirms its position that the withdrawal of Russian troops from Latvia and Estonia must be carried in accordance with the requirements of the international community, which are indicated in the 47/21 resolution of the United Nations and Article 15 of the CSCE 1992 Final Document." "Lithuania fully supports Estonia in its efforts to achieve a speedy withdrawal of the Russian army." The ministry expressed hope that Estonia and Russia will find mutually acceptable ways to resume bilateral talks and that Russian troops will leave Estonian territory by Aug. 31.
